VII    PRELIMINARY ASSESSMENT OF THE SITUATION



A    The refrigeration supervisor will assume the role of Response Team Leader ASAP.  Incoming aid will work within the ICS structure established by the HazMat Response Incident Commander working within the response chart provided in the appendix.  He shall also initiate and maintain a log of events during an emergency. The following initial information should be added to the checklist 

during the preliminary assessment of the situation:



1. Assessment of pre-incident site condition (condition of iced areas, surface 

                runoff, ground condition and containment capability and ambient 

                environmental conditions);



2. Date and time of incident (as accurately as possible);



3. Name of substance involved;



4. Ammonia concentrations measured using the ammonia detectors;



5. Estimated volume or weight of substance involved;



6. Estimated duration of release;





7. Cause of incident, if known;



8. Names of persons and agencies contacted, time contacted, description of conversation and report numbers issued; and



9. Record of control measures taken (include times of action when possible).



B    The EM will assume the role of Planning / Finance Chief unless the assistant can fill these positions and the EM is moved to the Unified IC Position. He/she assesses  possible hazards both direct and indirect to human health and/or the environment or property both inside and outside of the plant 







VIII    TERMINATION AND FOLLOW-UP ACTIVITIES



A    Incident Documentation/Reporting Requirements



1. A written report may be required to be submitted to the Okanogan County Local Emergency Planning Committee, Department of Ecology and the National Response Center, as soon as practicable, after the initial reporting of an ammonia release. The agency will advise you  if they need a written report.



